1. It doesn't matter the size of the file, as the loops are well written and can deal with any amount of data.
2. There is no universal size, as long as the methods are well written, it can continue to grow indefinitely.
3. As the word frequency increases, so does the chain length.
4. The algorithm did not account for punctuation. So words with periods after them were counted seperately than the same word without the period.
5. A simple, ordered approach made my hash table work. It had two choices, create a new slot or update an existing one.
6. I had no real trouble on this assignment.
7. The hash code is the most important part, if that is poorly designed, the hash table will not work right.